<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-26T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-26T15:00:00-05:00" n="176" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d176">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/2721: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Lane</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-26T15:00:00-05:00">May 26,
                                    1942—3 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 6:54 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>700. My 687, May 22, 7 p.m. In conversation with President-elect López
                            last evening I referred to oral arrangement with President Santos to
                            permit our forces enter Colombian waters in event of emergency. López
                            expressed approval of this arrangement and said he would gladly continue
                            it during his administration as well as any <pb facs="0168" n="154" xml:id="pg_154"/> other arrangements which we might have with Santos
                            for efficient prosecution of the war.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Panama for information of General Andrews.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lane</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>